# calc_fraction_sum.numos — type 1/2 + 1/3, evaluate, screenshot, ASSERT 5/6.
#
# Exercises VPAM fraction templates and cursor navigation. In NumOS the division
# key IS the fraction key (KeyCode::DIV -> insertFraction, CalculationApp.cpp:344),
# so `FRAC` is a script alias for `/`. insertFraction() captures the digit on the
# left as the numerator and drops the cursor into the denominator
# (CursorController.cpp:361-391); RIGHT then exits the fraction back to baseline.
#
# Phase 4B-C semantic proof: the exact value NumOS computes for 1/2 + 1/3 is the
# reduced fraction 5/6. The probe's canonical text form of CalculationApp's
# ExactVal (num/den) is "5/6" — confirmed empirically by running this fixture
# (assert_result prints actual='5/6'). We assert that COMPUTED value here; no OCR,
# no pixel matching. Visual correctness of the rendered 2D fraction remains the
# separate human-gated golden flow (Phase 4B-A/B).
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/calc_fraction_sum.numos \
#           --frames 1400 --screenshot out/calc_fraction_sum.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "calc_fraction_sum: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

key ENTER
wait 60

# 1/2  : type 1, FRAC captures it as numerator, type 2 into the denominator,
#        RIGHT exits the fraction.
key 1
key FRAC
key 2
key RIGHT

key +

# 1/3
key 1
key FRAC
key 3
key RIGHT

key ENTER
wait 120

# Screenshot first so the artifact exists even if an assertion later fails.
screenshot out/calc_fraction_sum.ppm
log "calc_fraction_sum: screenshot captured"

# Semantic assertions (Phase 4B-C): Calculation active, no eval error, and the
# computed value is the reduced fraction 5/6.
assert_app Calculation
assert_no_error
assert_result 5/6
log "calc_fraction_sum: assertions passed (result == 5/6)"
